==Alternatives to avoid Wikipedia's [[WP:PEIS|Post-expand include size]] limit==
Pages with many flag icons may come close to or exceed Wikipedia's [[WP:PEIS|Post-expand include size]] limit.  In these cases consider using modules or module-wrapper templates instead:
* {{tl|flagg}} is a simple wrapper for [[Module:Flagg]]: For basic use, <code>{{{{BASEPAGENAME}}<nowiki>|</nowiki>''athlete's name''<nowiki>|</nowiki>''country code or name''<nowiki>}}</nowiki></code> can be replaced with <code><nowiki>{{flagg|unaep|</nowiki>''country code or name''<nowiki>|</nowiki>preftext=''athlete's name''<nowiki>}}</nowiki></code>. To use IOC country codes, replace <code>unaep</code> with <code>unaepi</code>.
* {{ml|flag|athlete}} is a wrapper for [[Module:Flagg]] that can further reduce sizes when invoked directly. For basic use, <code>{{{{BASEPAGENAME}}<nowiki>|</nowiki>''athlete's name''<nowiki>|</nowiki>''country code or name''<nowiki>}}</nowiki></code> can be replaced with <code><nowiki>{{#invoke:flag|athlete|</nowiki>''athlete's name''<nowiki>|</nowiki>''country code or name''<nowiki>}}</nowiki></code>.  To use IOC country codes, add {{para|opts|i}}.

==See also==
*[[Template:Flag team]], a similar template useful for entire teams instead of individual names
*[[Template:Flag medalist]] a similar template with expanded country names
*[[:en:Template:Flag link medalist|Template:Flag link medalist]] a similar template with expanded country names and country info on one line
*[[Template:Flag]] and [[Template:Flag icon]] for additional discussion about flag variations
*[[Template:Flag IOC athlete]], a similar template for use with athletes at the Olympics
*[[:en:Template:Flag link athlete|Template:Flag link athlete]], a similar template to provide links to countries at editions of athletics championships

